The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 October is 81,940 (9,444.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 October, there were 2,570 new confirmed cases (296.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 October, there were 2,538 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (32 extra cases).
